post_text:
Thank you Note
Dear Leap Faculty,

I wanted to reach out to you guys and let you know that I will be Attending #Penn State University to further my education while also playing college baseball. This year has been the best year ever, and I cannot thank each and every one of you enough for all the things you have done for me!! Even though, the year was cut short and we did not get to experience some of the fun things planned I will hold on to each and every memory we made. I will continue to work hard and prosper. I will always be a Leap Academy Lion forever.

Sedale Nixon

post_text: Congratulations to our LEAP Scholars Sedale will be pursuing a degree in Criminal Justice with a minor in Sociology, and he hopes to work within the legal system to fight for social justice. Before committing to Penn State University, Sedale considered scholarship offers from over a dozen prestigious colleges and universities including the University of Miami, Temple University, and Rutgers University. Sedale is a member of the Business Cohort in the Early College Program, he is also a dual-enrollment participant, taking additional college coursework outside of the Early College Program to gain more credits.

Our 5th to 9th grade students put on a spectacular Black History Extravaganza under the direction of 8th grade science teacher and Hampton University Alum, Ms. Booker. Showcasing fashion, spoken word poetry, song, dance and live sketching, the show explored themes of resistance throughout various important eras in Black history.

Thank you Ms. Booker, teachers, parents, and students who worked together to stage a great performance!

Prevention Information for Other Coronaviruses

How to protect yourself.
There are currently no vaccines available to protect you against human coronavirus infection. You may be able to reduce your risk of infection by doing the following:
‚Ä¢ wash your hands often with soap and water for at least 20 seconds
‚Ä¢ avoid touching your eyes, nose, or mouth with unwashed hands
‚Ä¢ avoid close contact with people who are sick
For information about hand washing, see CDC‚Äôs Clean Hands Save Lives!
How to protect others
If you have cold-like symptoms, you can help protect others by doing the following
‚Ä¢ stay home while you are sick
‚Ä¢ avoid close contact with others
‚Ä¢ cover your mouth and nose with a tissue when you cough or sneeze, then throw the tissue in the trash and wash your hands
‚Ä¢ clean and disinfect objects and surfaces

post_text: In Mathematical Physics, students used the movement of a bowling ball to help visualize and calculate average speed. Students marked meter intervals to stand at to help keep time while another student pushed the bowling ball down a ramp. The students used three trials to calculate an absolute average time for each group then graphed their results to compare to other groups. #Teachertuesday #enrollatleap #leapexcellence
